ActFarm Income Protection Act
SubjectRegulations Repealing Certain Regulations Under the Farm Income Protection Act (Miscellaneous Program)
PrecisRegulations Repealing CERTAIN REGULATIONS UNDER THE FARM INCOME PROTECTION ACT (MISCELLANEOUS PROGRAM) in order to repeal seventy-three spent regulations made under Farm Income Protection Act and its predecessor legislation, the Agricultural Stabilization Act, and one regulation made under the authority of the Western Grain Stabilization Act to streamline the regulatory base, remove regulatory clutter, clarify applicable regulations, reduce stakeholder confusion and respond to concerns raised by the Standing Joint Committee for the Scrutiny of Regulations.
